<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-19T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00/794: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-19T16:00:00-04:00">February 19, 1936—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 20—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>21. Colonel Franco arrived at Asunción at 3 o’clock. It is understood
                            that he traveled in a plane chartered by the Buenos Aires newspaper <hi rend="italic">Crítica</hi>. It is probable that efforts to form a
                            provisional government will begin at once.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>